      "content": "Sure, I can help you with that! You can use the `str.replace()` method in pandas to remove those unwanted characters and empty strings. Here's a script that should do the trick:\n\n```python\nimport pandas as pd\n\n# Load your protein sequence data into a pandas dataframe\ndf = pd.read_csv('protein_sequences.csv')\n\n# Define a function to clean the sequences\ndef clean_sequence(seq):\n    # Remove non-ascii characters and empty strings\n    cleaned_seq = seq.replace('[^a-zA-Z]', '').replace('', '').strip()\n    return cleaned_seq\n\n# Apply the function to the 'sequence' column\ndf['sequence'] = df['sequence'].apply(clean_sequence)\n\n# Save the cleaned dataframe to a new CSV file\ndf.to_csv('cleaned_protein_sequences.csv', index=False)\n```\n\nThis script will remove any non-ascii characters and empty strings from your protein sequences, leaving only the valid ones. It will then save the cleaned dataframe to a new CSV file. Hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.",
